  introLines:
  - I knew it! The government grid finally collapsed!
  - Where are your hazmat suits? This radiation level must be off the charts
  answerWhatHappenedBefore: I finished cleaning up the flour from the kitchen, lay
    down in my favorite armchair for a tiny afternoon nap, and woke up looking at
    your beautiful face
  answerWhatKindOfLife: A full house, a warm oven, and lots of love. I spent my days
    making sure nobody in my neighborhood ever went to bed hungry
  answerWhatWasYourJob: I raised five children, twelve grandchildren, and fed every
    stray cat and college student on my block for fifty years
  answerWhatHappenedClothes: My shirt is covered in flour and powdered sugar. I was
    baking all morning, you see
  answerWhyHaveItem: I brought this fresh burger because you look like you need a
    proper meal! Purgatory is no place to keep an empty stomach
